		"description": "## About this Collection\n\nThis collection provides view-only access to a subset of MEDITECH's US Core FHIR API resources for sandbox testing. It is intended to help vendors quickly explore common requests and responses using test data.\n\nFor additional guidance on endpoints, workflows, and authentication, please refer to the [Greenfield Portal](https://greenfield.meditech.com).\n\n## Data Privacy & Usage Disclaimer\n\n- This collection is provided for testing in the Greenfield Workspace environment only.\n    \n- Do not use real patient data or any Protected Health Information (PHI).\n    \n- Payloads and requests are intended to validate structure, logic and authentication flows using test data.\n    \n- Postman is not HIPAA-compliant and does not guarantee secure handling of PHI.\n    \n- Client credentials are provisioned for sandbox use and must not be shared outside your authorized integration team.\n    \n- This collection is MEDITECH proprietary material and is provided for your organization's internal use only. Redistribution or external sharing is not permitted.\n    \n- If you alter environment variables to point to a production endpoint, you are solely responsible for ensuring compliance with your organization's privacy, security, and regulatory obligations.\n    \n\n## Reporting Access Issues\n\nIf you experience login problems with your registered Google ID or cannot access the Greenfield Portal, you may email [greenfieldinfo@meditech.com](https://mailto:greenfieldinfo@meditech.com).\n\n**Please note:** This email is for access issues only. All other sandbox questions should be addressed using the published documentation and FAQs. No dedicated support is provided for sandbox testing.",
